on one's reputation
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:Construction: to do, perform, accomplish, etc. something on one's reputation, to do the `near impossible', to accomplish without visible means, etc. against expectation or `the odds' ca1953 Christmas Charlie Buchanan, rabbiter, Bluff Station, Clarence Valley, remarks of trampers who have used a difficult and treacherous track: `You came round there on your reputation'.
